Bring a medium #pot{} of @salt{pinch}ed water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and halve @cucumber{1}, thinly slice crosswise into half-moons. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Cut @broccoli{1} into bite-size pieces if necessary.

In a small pot, combine @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

In a small #bowl{}, combine cucumber, @rice wine vinegar{10%teaspoon}, 1 tsp sugar (2 tsp for 4 servings), a pinch of salt, and as many @Korean chili flakes{1%teaspoon} as you like; set aside to pickle.

> TIP: Divide cucumber and pickling liquid between two small bowls; add chili flakes to one bowl and keep the other mild.

Once water is boiling, add @ramen noodles{4.5%ounce} to #pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, ~{1-2%minutes}. Drain, then rinse noodles thoroughly under cold water, ~{30%seconds}. Toss with a drizzle of @cooking oil{} and set aside.

> TIP: If you added any other items to your meal (apps, sides, and/or dessert), you can get started on them now!

Open package of @diced skinless dark meat chicken{10%ounce} and drain off any excess liquid.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and scallion whites in a single layer and cook, undisturbed, until lightly browned, about ~{2%minutes}. Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until chicken is browned and cooked through, ~{2-4%minutes} more.

Stir in @sweet soy glaze{1/2%cup}, @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%ounce}, and 1/4 cup water (1/2 cup for 4 servings). Cook until sauce has slightly reduced, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Meanwhile, place broccoli in a large microwave-safe bowl; cover tightly with #plastic wrap{} and poke a few holes in wrap. Microwave until broccoli is tender, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Carefully uncover (watch out for steam!) and toss broccoli with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Serve noodles, chicken, broccoli, pickles (draining first), @crispy fried onions{1}, @peanuts{1/2%ounce}, and scallion greens family style so everyone can make their own noodle bowls!

Fluff rice with a fork; serve alongside noodle bar.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.